% ================================================================
%  references.bib — sample bibliography for CS Senior Research
% ================================================================
%  Place this file in the same directory as your paper.md.
%  The YAML header already points to it:   bibliography: references.bib
%
%  BibTeX entry types you'll use most often:
%    @article       — journal paper
%    @inproceedings — conference paper
%    @misc          — websites, software, preprints, datasets
%    @book          — textbook or monograph
%    @phdthesis     — dissertation
%
%  Tips:
%    - The cite key (e.g., smith2024) is what you use in your paper:
%        [@smith2024]         →  [1]  (IEEE style)
%        [@smith2024, p. 5]   →  [1, p. 5]
%        [@smith2024; @jones2025]  →  [1], [2]
%    - Google Scholar → click "Cite" → "BibTeX" to auto-generate entries
%    - Keep cite keys consistent: lastNameYear (e.g., lecun2015)
% ================================================================


% ── Conference paper ─────────────────────────────────────────────
